==English==
===Noun===
'''beach''' ([[beaches]])

# A horizontal strip of land, usually [[sand]]y, adjoining [[water]]

====Antonyms====
* [[depths]]
* [[peak]]
* [[valley]]

====Synonyms====
* [[cove]]
* [[sand]]
* [[surf]]

====Example usage====
* '''1988:''' “Up and down, the '''beach''' lay empty for miles.”  -''Second Son'', Robert Ferro

====Slang usage====
# To describe something/someone as being desirable, fun, or cool.
* "Wow, Kirstie, that party was so '''beach'''!"
* "Nice, Peter! You look very '''beach''' today!"
* "I hope today will be '''beach''' since yesterday was so lame."

